The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Satyam sets ADS price at $21.50

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, May 11: Satyam Computer Services has priced its sponsored American depository shares (ADS) at $21.50 apiece. It has converted around 2.6 crore shares to ADS.

 The maximum size of the offering is 3 crore shares and the transaction amount is put at $280 million. Satyam Computers today said the underwriters have an option to purchase up to 1,956,520 additional American depository shares, representing 3,913,040 shares, within seven days of the pricing. 

 It also said the net proceeds will be returned to all the selling shareholders within 30 days of the closing of the offer. 

 The global co-ordinator for the offering was Merrill Lynch International and the joint bookrunners were Merrill Lynch International, J. P. Morgan Securities Inc and Citigroup Global Markets Limited. 

 Bear, Stearns amp; Co Inc and Lehman Brothers Inc were joint lead managers and Gilford Securities Inc and Janney Montgomery Scott LLC were co-managers. Enam Financial Consultants Pvt Ltd acted as the Indian financial adviser for the offer. 

 After the conversion, the ADS holding in Satyam Computers will rise to around 20 per cent from 10.65 per cent at present.

 As on March 31, 2005, the promoters held a 15.67 per cent stake in the company, institutional investors had 66.96 per cent and Indian public 4.47 per cent. The other shareholders included private corporate bodies, and NRIs/OCBs apart from the ADS holders.

 Besides Satyam, ICICI Bank and Infosys Technologies have announced such offerings to improve their liquidity in overseas markets. 

 Domestic shareholders are also expected to benefit from the offering as they can earn an attractive premium to the local market price after tendering the shares.

 ICICI Bank had in March this year, priced its sponsored ADS offering at $21.11 apiece. 




